FBIS4-7058 "dreas080_l_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-080 Daily Report 21 Apr 1994 Philippines Ramos To Expand East ASEAN Growth Area Ramos To Expand East ASEAN Growth Area BK2604033994 Manila BUSINESS WORLD in English 21 Apr 94 p 2 BK2604033994 Manila BUSINESS WORLD English BFN [Text] President Ramos has approved the adoption of several measures aimed at accelerating the implementation of the Brunei Darussalam, Indonesia, Malaysia, Philippines-East ASEAN Growth Area (BIMP-EAGA), reporters learned yesterday. During the Cabinet meeting last Tuesday, the president directed the immediate establishment of a Philippine council to pursue the implementation of the BIMP-EAGA. He also ordered various government agencies to undertake activities for the operationalization of the EAGA and to identify additional flagship development projects in Mindanao to support the same. To boost awareness and speed up implementation, Mr. Ramos likewise ordered the creation of additional investment and tourism promotion councils (ITPCs) in major cities of Mindanao to conduct awareness campaign on the BIMP-EAGA. Currently, there are ITPCs in Davao, Zamboanga, and Cagayan de Oro. The additional councils will be located in Cotabato, Gen. Santos, Butuan, and Iligan. The EAGA was formally launched last March in Davao City.
